  <num>1-612.10</num>
  <heading>Termination of PFML Bank use.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>The use of the PFML Bank transferred hours shall terminate on the date that the:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>Leave recipient's employment terminates;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Leave recipient is no longer experiencing a qualifying medical leave event or qualifying family leave event; or</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>The 12-month period specified in <cite path="§1-612.05|(f)">§ 1-612.05(f)</cite> expires.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>Unused transferred leave shall not be subject to any form of lump-sum leave payment upon the leave recipient's separation from employment.</text>
  </para>
